meta.currencySpeechRule: Speak prices as natural phrases (e.g., two hundred ninety-nine dollars and ninety-nine cents). Never say 'point'.

start.say: Hi, this is Alex with Health America. How are you doing today?

reason_for_call.say: The reason I’m calling is to follow up on the health information we sent you. Did you get that okay?

hotline_offer.say: Absolutely. Our customer care and reorder line is one eight six six… three seven nine… five one three one. I’ll repeat that normally: 1-866-379-5131. I can also help you right now—would you like me to take care of this for you?

farewell_soft.say: Thank you for your time today. If you need anything or want to reorder later, we’re at 1-866-379-5131.

qualify_intro.say: Great—let me ask a few quick questions to better understand your health. I’ll keep it simple and quick.

q1_joint_1.say: Do you have any arthritis or joint stiffness?

q1_joint_2.say: Which joints bother you most—knees, hips, hands, back?

q1_joint_3.say: How long has that been going on?

q1_joint_4.say: Is the discomfort worse in the morning or at night?

q2_pain_1.say: On a scale of one to ten, what’s your pain level today?

q2_pain_2.say: What tends to make it better or worse?

q3_age_1.say: If you don’t mind me asking, how old are you?

q3_age_2.say: You sound great—much younger than that.

q4_diabetes_1.say: Do you deal with diabetes or elevated blood sugar?

q4_diabetes_2.say: Is it type one or type two—if applicable?

q4_diabetes_3.say: Is it managed? What do you take for it?

q4_diabetes_4.say: Do you monitor at home? Any recent A1C?

q5_energy_1.say: How are your daily energy levels—mornings versus afternoons?

q6_breathing_1.say: Any breathing issues or shortness of breath?

q7_sleep_1.say: Do you feel your sleep is restful?

q7_sleep_2.say: How many hours do you usually get?

q7_sleep_3.say: Trouble falling asleep, staying asleep, or waking too early?

q8_senses_1.say: How are your hearing and vision lately?

q9_weight_1.say: Are you happy with your current weight?

q9_weight_2.say: About how many pounds would you like to lose, if any?

q10_bp_1.say: How is your blood pressure lately?

q10_bp_2.say: Are you taking anything for it?

q11_cognitive_1.say: Any memory or balance issues—brain fog or trouble focusing?

q11_cognitive_2.say: Is it better or worse at certain times of day?

q12_immune_1.say: How is your immune system—do you get frequent colds or sinus issues?

q12_immune_2.say: Any allergies that flare up seasonally?

needs_confirm.say: From what you’ve shared, we’ll focus first on {{primary_goal}}—and you also mentioned {{secondary_goal}}. That matches what I’m seeing.

kb_select.say: Let me match you with the best fit from our line.

value_story_intro.say: I’ll keep this simple and specific to you.

value_story_pitch.say: Based on what you’ve shared, the best fit is {{primary_product}}. It supports {{benefits_to_outcomes}}—for example, {{key_benefits}}—so you can {{tangible_outcome}}. Many customers also pair it with {{upsell_product}} to {{upsell_benefit}} to accelerate results.

trial_close.say: That sounds like exactly what you were hoping to find, doesn’t it?

offer_choice.say: Perfect. Would you like the single bottle, or the value pack that saves more per bottle?

price_menu.say: Here are the options: membership monthly, one-time, three-pack, six-pack, or annual twelve-pack. I’ll outline each clearly.

price_menu_detail.say: Membership is seventy-nine ninety-nine per month; one-time is eighty-nine ninety-nine; three-pack is one hundred ninety-nine ninety-nine; six-pack two hundred ninety-nine ninety-nine; annual five hundred ninety-nine ninety-nine—no shipping fees and no taxes. Which fits best?

identity_intro.say: Great, I’ll take care of everything for you. I’ll capture the details clearly and confirm back as we go.

name_on_card.say: First, what’s your full name exactly as it appears on the card?

billing_street.say: What’s the billing street address for the card? Include apartment or unit if any.

billing_state.say: Billing state—please say the full state name.

shipping_same.say: Is the shipping address the same as the billing address?

shipping_state.say: Shipping state—please say the full state name.

contact_phone.say: What’s the best phone number for updates and delivery questions?

contact_email.say: What’s the best email for your receipt and tracking?

payment_method.say: Which payment method works best for you—card or bank?

payment_reassure.say: You’re fully covered by our money-back guarantee, and there are no shipping fees or taxes. We’ll keep this simple and quick.

card_number.say: Please read me the full card number. I’ll confirm it back once, grouped for accuracy.

card_cvc.say: CVC on the back of the card? You’ll say it once.

bank_account_name.say: What name is on the bank account?

postdate_check_entry.say: I can finalize this now. If you prefer a future date for billing, just let me know.

postdate_intro.say: Sure. Tell me the date you’d like us to run it—month, day, and year.

postdate_confirm.say: Great, I’ve secured your card ending {{last4}}. Nothing will process until {{run_date}} as you requested. I’ll send your confirmation to your email.

price_total.say: For your {{product_choice}}, your total comes to {{human_price}}—with no shipping fees and no taxes.

readback_confirm.say: Here’s what I have: {{primary_product}}{{upsell_suffix}} at {{human_price}}; shipping to {{ship_address_line}}; payment ending in {{last4}}. Is that all correct?

readback_clarify.say: No problem—what should I correct or update for you?

correct_details.say: Thank you. Let’s update that now.

capture_sale.say: Perfect—processing now. You’ll receive an email receipt and tracking.

create_order.say: Generating your order in our system.

closing_sale.say: Your order is confirmed. No shipping, no taxes, and your discount is locked in. Thank you for choosing Health America—you’re going to love the results. If you ever need anything or want to reorder, our number is 1-866-379-5131.

catch_all.say: I want to get this right for you. Could you say that a different way so I can help you faster?
